      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from class: SailPointObject
        We override equals so that two objects will compare equal if they have the same database id or unique name, but are different Java objects. This is necessary for Hibernate because caches commonly have to be cleared or objects from one session need to be used to match things loaded in a different session.

      • isHideAllowSelf

        public boolean isHideAllowSelf()
        Return true if this QuickLink is hiding self requests. This can be used for self-service QuickLinks that do not wish to allow self-requests and will typically be used in conjunction with isForceAllowOthers().

      • isHideAllowOthers

        public boolean isHideAllowOthers()
        Return true if this QuickLink is hiding requests for others. This can be used for non-self-service QuickLinks that do not wish to allow requests for others and will typically be used in conjunction with isForceAllowSelf().

      • isForceAllowSelf

        public boolean isForceAllowSelf()
        Return true if this QuickLink should allow self requests. This can be used for non-self-service QuickLinks that require self-requests.

      • isForceAllowOthers

        public boolean isForceAllowOthers()
        Return true if this QuickLink should allow requests for others. This can be used for self-service QuickLinks that require requesting for others.
